---
// SlicedLabs · legal · © 2026 SlicedLabs — Refund Policy
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
const updated = "June 22, 2026";
---
<Base title="Refund Policy — SlicedLabs" description="Returns, refunds, and cancellations for SlicedLabs products, workshops, and memberships.">
  <section class="wrap" style="max-width:46rem; padding-block:clamp(2.5rem,7vw,4rem);">
    <p class="mono" data-reveal>legal</p>
    <h1 data-reveal style="--i:1; font-size:clamp(2rem,6vw,3.4rem); margin:.3rem 0 0;"><span class="blend-text">Refund Policy</span></h1>
    <hr class="blade" data-reveal style="--i:2; max-width:10rem; margin:1.2rem 0 1.2rem;" />
    <p class="mono" style="color:var(--muted); margin:0 0 1.4rem;">Last updated: {updated}</p>
    <div class="glass island" data-reveal style="margin-bottom:1.6rem;">
      <p style="margin:0; color:var(--muted);"><strong style="color:var(--ink);">A note.</strong> This is a good-faith starting template — not legal advice. Have a qualified attorney review it before you rely on it.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="prose" data-reveal>
      <p>We want you to be happy with what you buy. Here's how refunds work by product type. To start any request, use the <a href="/contact">contact page</a> with your order details.</p>

      <h2>Merchandise (physical, print-on-demand)</h2>
      <p>Because items are made to order, we don't accept returns for buyer's remorse or sizing. <strong>However, if your item arrives damaged, defective, or wrong, we'll replace it or refund it</strong> — contact us within <strong>30 days</strong> of delivery with a photo of the issue.</p>

      <h2>Digital products (playbooks, drops)</h2>
      <p>Digital goods are delivered instantly and are generally <strong>non-refundable</strong> once accessed. If something is broken or not as described, contact us and we'll make it right.</p>

      <h2>Workshops &amp; events</h2>
      <p>Cancel at least <strong>48 hours</strong> before the session for a full refund. Inside 48 hours, tickets are non-refundable but transferable to a future session. If <em>we</em> cancel, you'll get a full refund or a reschedule.</p>

      <h2>Memberships</h2>
      <p>You can <strong>cancel any time</strong>; cancellation stops future renewals and your access continues to the end of the current paid period. We don't pro-rate or refund the current period unless required by law. Accidental renewal? Contact us within 7 days and we'll work it out.</p>

      <h2>How refunds are issued</h2>
      <p>Approved refunds go back to your original payment method via Stripe, typically within 5–10 business days depending on your bank.</p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>Start a request via the <a href="/contact">contact page</a> — include your order number and what happened.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
